[Patient] Can you give me recommendations for managing my fluid intake with heart failure?
[Educator] Limit salt intake and monitor your fluid intake daily to avoid fluid overload.
[Patient] How much water should I be drinking each day?
[Educator] Aim for about 8-10 cups of water per day, but adjust based on your body's needs.
[Patient] What should I do if I notice swelling in my ankles or difficulty breathing?
[Educator] Contact your healthcare provider immediately if you experience these symptoms - they may indicate fluid overload.
[Patient] Are there any specific foods I should avoid to help manage my fluid intake?
[Educator] Limit high-sodium foods like processed meats, canned soups, and fast food to help control fluid retention.
[Patient] How can I track my fluid intake to make sure I am staying within the recommended limits?
[Educator] Keep a journal or use a smartphone app to track your fluid intake throughout the day.